## Operational Definitions

**v* (Ze steady-state):** HI(t→∞) = 0.456 ± 0.05. Measured as mean HI across 10 independent simulation runs (30 seeds each).
- If HI ≥ 0.53 → Ze confirmed
- If HI 0.51-0.53 → inconclusive
- If HI ≤ 0.51 → Ze rejected

**χ_Ze (integrated metric):** HI(t) / (1 + τ_conv/T). Combines hierarchy strength and speed.

**Falsifiability (updated):**
- BioSense v*: if mean v* ≠ 0.456 ± 0.05 in n=30 healthy volunteers, reject
- MCAOA: if cross-counter R² < 0.3 in all tissues, reject
- Ze-Hierarchy: if HI ≤ 0.51 in 10 runs, reject
